sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant R as Router (Claude)
    participant SM as Skill Manifest
    participant S as SKILL.md
    participant REF as references/
    participant MCP as MCP Servers
    participant OUT as Structured Output

    U->>R: "Generate my standup"

    Note over R,SM: Phase 1 — Intent Matching
    R->>SM: Match utterance against<br/>skill descriptions (YAML frontmatter)
    SM-->>R: Best match: engineering:standup<br/>(description triggers on "standup")

    Note over R,S: Phase 2 — Progressive Disclosure
    R->>S: Load SKILL.md body<br/>(≤3000 words, imperative instructions)
    S-->>R: Standalone + Supercharged modes,<br/>output format, connector refs

    alt References needed
        R->>REF: Load references/*.md<br/>(patterns, advanced docs)
        REF-->>R: Detailed supplementary context
    end

    Note over R,MCP: Phase 3 — Tool Integration
    R->>R: Check CONNECTORS.md:<br/>~~source control, ~~project tracker,<br/>~~chat, ~~CI/CD

    alt MCP Connected (Supercharged Mode)
        par Parallel MCP Calls
            R->>MCP: github → list_commits(since: yesterday)
            R->>MCP: linear → list_issues(assignee: me, updated: today)
            R->>MCP: slack → search_messages(channel: #eng)
        end
        MCP-->>R: Commits, PR reviews, ticket moves
        MCP-->>R: Issue status changes, new assignments
        MCP-->>R: Relevant team discussions
    else No MCP (Standalone Mode)
        R->>U: "What did you work on yesterday?"
        U-->>R: Free-text activity summary
    end

    Note over R,OUT: Phase 4 — Response Generation
    R->>OUT: Structure into Yesterday / Today / Blockers
    OUT-->>U: Formatted standup with ticket refs
